Four years ago, Miché Solomon discovered that the mom she’d known and loved all these years was actually her kidnapper. In the years that followed, Zephany Nurse’s identity and the “new” name she was given by her parents was withheld by the court. But the court order has recently been lifted, at her own insistence, and the mom-of-two is ready to face the world. YOU recently sat down with the 22-year-old and spoke to her about her decision to finally disclose her identity. Check out the full clip below.  Read the full story in the latest YOU, in stores now. 